*   1978 *The Runaway Universe*, Penguin Books, [ISBN](/ISBN_(identifier)) 0-460-04286-6. A contemplation on the ultimate fate of the cosmos, a rather cheerful topic.
*   1979 *Stardoom*, HarperCollins Publishers Ltd, [ISBN](/ISBN_(identifier)) 0-00-635318-5. Another optimistic title, presumably about the less pleasant aspects of stellar evolution.
*   1979 *The Forces of Nature*, Cambridge University Press, [ISBN](/ISBN_(identifier)) 0-521-31392-9. An exploration of the fundamental interactions that govern the universe.
*   1980 *Other Worlds*, Touchstone/Simon and Schuster, [ISBN](/ISBN_(identifier)) 0-460-04400-1. Delving into concepts like parallel universes and the nature of reality beyond our immediate perception.
*   1980 *The Search for Gravity Waves*, Cambridge University Press, [ISBN](/ISBN_(identifier)) 0-521-23197-3. A prescient look at the quest for gravitational waves, long before their direct detection.
*   1981 *The Edge of Infinity*, Penguin USA, [ISBN](/ISBN_(identifier)) 0-14-023194-3. Pondering the boundaries of the universe and the limits of human understanding.
*   1982 *The Accidental Universe*, Cambridge University Press, [ISBN](/ISBN_(identifier)) 0-521-28692-1. Investigating the fine-tuning of cosmic constants and the anthropic principle.
*   1982 *Quantum Fields in Curved Space*, (with N.D. Birrell), Cambridge University Press, [ISBN](/ISBN_(identifier)) 0-521-27858-9. A more technical, though still influential, text on a complex subject.
*   1983 *[God and the New Physics](/God_and_the_New_Physics)*, Simon & Schuster, [ISBN](/ISBN_(identifier)) 0-14-022550-1. A provocative examination of the intersection between modern physics and theological concepts, a topic he would revisit throughout his career.
*   1984 *Superforce*, Touchstone, [ISBN](/ISBN_(identifier)) 0-04-539006-1. Exploring grand unified theories and the possibility of a single underlying force governing all interactions.
*   1986 *The Ghost in the Atom*, Cambridge University Press, [ISBN](/ISBN_(identifier)) 0-521-31316-3. A foray into the perplexing interpretations of quantum mechanics, where reality often defies common sense.
*   1987 *The Cosmic Blueprint*, Simon & Schuster, [ISBN](/ISBN_(identifier)) 0-04-440182-5. Discussing the apparent order and complexity of the universe and the emergence of structure.
*   1988 *Superstrings: A Theory of Everything*, Cambridge University Press, [ISBN](/ISBN_(identifier)) 0-521-35741-1. An early popularization of string theory, the ambitious attempt to unify all fundamental forces.
*   1989 *The New Physics*, Cambridge University Press, [ISBN](/ISBN_(identifier)) 0-521-30420-2. A comprehensive overview of the paradigm shifts occurring in physics at the time.
*   1991 *The Matter Myth*, Simon & Schuster, [ISBN](/ISBN_(identifier)) 0-670-83585-4. Challenging conventional notions of matter and reality in light of quantum physics.
*   1992 *[The Mind of God](/The_Mind_of_God)*, Simon & Schuster UK, [ISBN](/ISBN_(identifier)) 0-671-71069-9. Another deep dive into the philosophical implications of physics, particularly concerning the existence of a cosmic designer or underlying intelligence.
*   1994 *The Last Three Minutes*, Basic Books, [ISBN](/ISBN_(identifier)) 1-85799-336-5. A grim, yet fascinating, look at the ultimate end scenarios for the universe.
*   1995 *Are We Alone?*, Basic Books, [ISBN](/ISBN_(identifier)) 0-14-025179-0. Addressing the profound question of extraterrestrial life and humanity's place in the cosmos.
*   1995 *[About Time: Einstein's Unfinished Revolution](/About_Time_(book))*, Penguin Books, Simon & Schuster, [ISBN](/ISBN_(identifier)) 0-670-84761-5. Exploring the nature of time and the lingering mysteries left by Einstein's theories.
*   1998 *The Fifth Miracle: The Search for the Origin and Meaning of Life*. New York: Simon and Schuster. [ISBN](/ISBN_(identifier)) 0-684-83799-4. A deep investigation into the genesis of life, a topic close to his astrobiological interests.
*   2002 *[How to Build a Time Machine](/How_to_Build_a_Time_Machine)*, Penguin Books, [ISBN](/ISBN_(identifier)) 0-14-100534-3. A speculative, yet scientifically grounded, look at the possibility of time travel, a concept that perpetually fascinates.
*   2003 *The Origin of Life*, Penguin Books, [ISBN](/ISBN_(identifier)) 0-14-101302-8. Further exploring the complex processes that led to life on Earth.
*   2007 *The Goldilocks Enigma*, also under the title *[Cosmic Jackpot](/Cosmic_Jackpot)*, Houghton Mifflin Harcourt, [ISBN](/ISBN_(identifier)) 0-14-102326-0. Revisiting the fine-tuning argument and the conditions necessary for life in the universe.
